-- Hong Kong Air Pollution Hits `Very High' Level at 143 in Central District
-- B y   D i r k   B e v e r i d g e
-- 2010-11-22T23:39:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/hong-kong-air-pollution-hits-very-high-level-at-143-in-central-district.html
Hong Kong’s Air Pollution Index was
a “very high” 143 at the Central district roadside monitoring
station, the city’s Environmental Protection Department said on
its website.  Roadside readings above 100 trigger a government warning
that people with heart or respiratory ailments should avoid
prolonged stays in heavy traffic areas.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dirk Beveridge at 
 dbeveridge1@bloomberg.net  